In the drawings, closely related parts have the same number but different alphabetic or numeric suffixes. The numbering system with each separate different figure number starts anew, so that the last two digits specify the part number. Thus, in a three digit number the first digit indicates the drawing number, and in a four digit number, the first and second number indicates the drawing number. Items with the same last two numbers usually have the same function in the different drawings.


